		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm with Tassoth on this one.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>My own thoughts on bards:  they are the busiest class to play.  I spend 90% of the time with both hands busy on the mouse or keyboard.  To play a bard well you really need to know the short cut keys.  I don't chat much except during downtime (and then not always).  Playing a bard requires constant attention or death will result.  Playing Bards require quick reaction time, good manual dexterity, and fast thinking.  Pre-planning is important since certain songs work better in some situations than others.  <br><br>The biggest advantage and disadvantage of the bard is that bards can do so much.  They are the most flexible of all the classes.  High and mid level bards are rare since most folk just give up in frustration.   Bards are not for &quot;hack 'n' slash&quot; players.  Bards need to be able to work well alone but also with a group.  There are times as a bard you will never lift a weapon but sit back with the casters and watch whats happening.  Other times you will never lift an instrument because you are too busy with weapons.<br><br>Bards are for adaptable players.  If don't like changing your mind set or concept of the game everytime you play then don't be a bard.  No other class is more challenging to play then a bard.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
